# Multi-App Server Blueprint

Purpose: standardize hosting multiple independent applications on one hardened server while preserving isolation and operational clarity.

## Objectives
- Host multiple apps on one server without cross-app blast radius.
- Keep one consistent AI-first workflow across all apps.
- Enforce shared operational/security baseline with per-app isolation.

## Core Architecture

### 1) Shared Host Foundation
- Harden host baseline and patch policy.
- Central runtime management.
- Central backup and monitoring targets.

### 2) Shared Edge Layer
- One domain strategy.
- One edge/tunnel strategy with multiple hostnames routed per app.
- No inbound router port forwarding.

### 3) Per-App Isolation Unit
Each app should have its own:
- Repository
- Compose project namespace
- Internal network(s)
- Database and volume(s)
- Secret set
- CI/verify workflow
- Deployment and rollback runbook

## Networking Model
- Shared edge ingress network.
- App-internal network per app.
- No cross-app internal traffic unless explicitly documented.

## App Onboarding Checklist
- [ ] Initialize app repo from standardization templates.
- [ ] Configure app-specific env/secrets.
- [ ] Configure app-specific compose/network/volume.
- [ ] Configure app-specific DNS/tunnel hostname.
- [ ] Execute smoke checks and verify gate.
- [ ] Register app in operational inventory.

## Multi-App Readiness Criteria
- Two or more apps independently deployable and recoverable.
- App-level verify gates and smoke runbooks in place.
- Backup/restore validated per app.
